-- Shanghai's Fang Says China Should Start Property Tax, Securities Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-15T23:56:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/shanghai-s-fang-says-china-should-start-property-tax-securities-reports.html

          
          
             A Chinese property tax would be
well-timed, the China Securities Journal cited Fang Xinghai,
director general of Shanghai’s financial services offices, as
saying.  
 Hong Kong’s introduction of yuan-denominated products will
not affect Shanghai as a financial center, the report said.  
          
          


  


        